<figureCitation id="132E1A84231AFFEBFC4382D4FBFAF865" box="[993,1083,1977,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="66.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,184,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 51. Litophyton nigrescens (Roxas, 1933), holotype SMF 61; a, lateral views polyp armature; b-c, abaxial point spindles; d, tentacle scales; e, lateral, adaxial, and polyp stalk scales; f, supporting bundle spindles, partly; g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk. Scale at h also applies to b-c, f-g, j; scale at d also applies to e." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765031/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Figs. 51</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E1A84231AFFEBFBE482D7FBAFF865" box="[1094,1134,1977,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 56" captionStartId="74.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURE 56. Litophyton type specimens: a, L. nigrescens (Roxas, 1933), holotype SMF 61; b, L. compactum (Verseveldt, 1966), holotype RMNH 2236; c, L. elongatum (K체kenthal, 1895), holotype SMF 62; d, L. pyramidalis (K체kenthal, 1895), holotype SMF 63; e, L. carnatum n. sp., holotype NTM C4100. Scales 1 cm, a, e natural size." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765041/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">56a</figureCitation>
) but differs in having much coarser, sparse tuberculation in the stalk sclerites.
</paragraph>
